or</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/12/02 4:18:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grouping: Play Mechanics vs Roleplaying</span><hr size=1> If you fight on the moon, you might have more problems getting a group, but its not so bad, I can normally find one. (except when your the odd man out or when a group is all good and your evil) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/12/02 4:34:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grouping: Play Mechanics vs Roleplaying</span><hr size=1> Bah.  If I join a group and they aren't roleplaying at all, I may or may not stay.  If they say &quot;whut lvl r u guyz&quot; then I disband and go solo something.  I have little patience for the idiotic of the world, much less the idiotic sharing this MMORPG.<br>
<br>
Personally, if I'm just hunting in the wilderness I /shout RUN! to the group and we make for the zone line quick like.  If other people are resting by the zone line, well, they should see the hordes coming and zone along with us.  If they don't, it's their fault.<br>
<br>
If I'm in a dungeon, I have a couple of hotkeys set up.  One /shouts &quot;Gain way or be shown Innoruuk's brand of love!&quot; and the other one is &quot;I'm sprinting for the exit and I'm being TRAINED!&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't think either one is particularly OOC, and one if not the other has always gotten the point across, be it Befallen, Blackburrow, or The Warrens.  I also have a /yell after each one, so people know the general direction I'm coming from, and can feel free to pull one or two mobs away should they feel like it.  These things together usually let people know I'm not just shouting &quot;DING!&quot; if they can't understand my language.<br>
<br>
What I do hate is inconsiderate people.  If you wander somewhere new and pull the whole dungeon down on yourself and get lots of people killed in the train, fine.  But next time you either shout or put me on /ignore because I'm going to be down your throat, whether you know my language or not.  And I don't agree with the philosophy one wood elf enlightened me with:  &quot;trains happen all the time here, dont hunt here if you dont want to die.  i dont have to yell&quot;<br>
<br>
Although I took out a few choice expletives (which were garbled), that is exactly quoted and a great example of selfishness.  It's funny because in The Warrens most people shout when coming up and unless alot of people are inexperienced (the floor is always littered with the bodies of level 5 elves) there usually isn't alot of deaths.  Compare that with Blackburrow where noone shouts EVER and people seem very fond of sitting right in the entrance just so people have a hard time getting around them.  Feh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 4:15:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grouping: Play Mechanics vs Roleplaying</span><hr size=1> There are also a lot of people that take the &quot;roleplaying-preferred&quot; theme of the server very seriously. My human druid would have little use for halfling rogues, let alone a halfling rogue that has decided to call himself Powwah.<br>
<br>
I spent too much time on Tallon Zek with people I couldn't stand using names like Powwah Killah, Powa Fista, and Powah Wangah. Obviously, I don't know you or the thought behind your name, but I'm just pointing out that I would be cautious associating with you without getting to know you first. The key to finding groups is getting to know people and making friends. It's much more effective than running around looking for pickup groups. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
(Lux Aeternam)<BR>
30th Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 5:13:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yeah, I bet Grim has it</span><hr size=1> Dunno why you chose it, but the name &quot;Powwah&quot; just screams &quot;d00d incoming, run for ur lives!&quot;  I'm not part of the RP-Gestopo, but that would be my first thought and knee-jerk reaction even on a normal blue server.  You'll have to work extra hard to convince people you don't have the d00d-plague with a name like Powwah.<br>
<br>
OTH, sometimes it's really hard to get a group.  Yesterday, I talked to 3 partials in Upper Guk -- one was Indigo Void (very nice RP, but they didn't like humans, so I stayed in character and didn't ask to group).  The other two just responded (more or less) &quot;we only want to group with ourselves&quot;.  Tried Sol-A.  Elven-blade group didn't even bother to answer my tell -- maybe they were all afk.  Other group was too high level.  Najena group claimed language barrier and full group (I've mastered all languages and there were 5 total in zone -- maybe someone off to sell).<br>
<br>
OTH, sometimes you zone in and are hit by a &quot;JOIN or DISBAND&quot; before you even speak.  It's definitely very weird for grouping.  I'd highly recommend a guild and I'm in the process of searching for one now.  Only progess so far is that I've crossed two off the list (yes, FV does have rude d00d guilds) and had some good brief casual contact with a few others.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 11:24:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Finding Groups</span><hr size=1> A guild is a good way to go.  Barring that, keep a list of friends in your level range and ask then if they have groups you can join, and make sure to invite them in return when you can.  Get used to going where your friends are, rather than walking into a zone and assuming there is going to be a group at or near your favorite camp.  Pick up groups are not unknown, but they are the exception rather than the rule.  Make friends and keep them.  That's the best advise I know how to give.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
